news.title: Karnataka government drafts policy for sustainable management of C&D waste
news.para: The policy is expected to reuse and recycle at least 50% of C&D waste generated in municipal corporations’ limits by December 2026. It will also confirm that at least 50% of C&D waste generated in ULBs (Urban local bodies) in Karnataka will be reused or recycled by December 2027

news.title: Mumbai police arrested real estate agent for altering plot reservation
news.para: The crime branch arrested the agent, Narshim Puttawallu (50), a resident of Charkop in Malad. Earlier, the Goregaon police had arrested Rupa Bharat Mehta (64) and filed a chargesheet against her.

news.title: Karnataka considers mandating Aadhaar ID for property registration
news.para: An official said, “To prevent fraudulent registrations through fake documents and identities, the Stamp and Registration Department has mandated submitting one of these three personal documents, including Aadhaar verification, for registration since September.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government awaits center's clearance for Visakhapatnam metro project
news.para: Minister for municipal administration P Narayana said that the works will be launched after getting clearances from the Centre.

news.title: Flats with interlinking passage cannot have separate electricity connections: TNERC
news.para: The ombudsman rejected the argument of the petitioner, S Manimekalai of Mylapore, that the internal passage linking two tenements was only a temporary arrangement as they were senior citizens.

news.title: Mumbai: IL&FS headquarters' sale stuck over valuation
news.para: Chronos, which was the winning bidder, has challenged the move in National Company Law Tribunal, which has restrained IL&FS from creating any third-party interest in TIFC or insisting that the revised valuation be accepted or rejected by the buyer.

news.title: Morgan Stanley, others acquires 6.8% stake in PNB Housing for Rs 1,664 crore
news.para: According to bulk deal data available on the National Stock Exchange (NSE), Morgan Stanley through its arm Morgan Stanley Asia Singapore purchased over 1.42 crore shares or a 5.4 per cent stake in PNB Housing in two transactions.

news.title: Gurugram: Eight illegal structures demolished in Aravali protected zone
news.para: The area where the action was taken comes under the Aravali notification of 1992, which prohibits construction and felling of trees without permission in protected areas. Non-forest activities are not allowed on land classified as ‘gair mumkin pahad' (uncultivable hill).

news.title: SEBI eases lock-in rules for InvITs and REITs under employee benefit schemes
news.para: Standardizing quarterly reporting format, Sebi has mandated that Bharat InvITs Association and Indian REITs Association specify a uniform format for quarterly reports and compliance certificates.

news.title: NARCL increases offer for Jaiprakash Associates' debt to Rs 12,000 crore
news.para: Last month, NARCL made a fresh ₹12,000 crore bid to take over the ₹54,000 crore debt, increasing its earlier ₹10,000 core offer in March. The fresh offer follows a valuation exercise carried out by the bad loan aggregator after it had given its first offer, two people with direct knowledge of the matter said.

news.title: Ashiana Housing posts net loss of Rs 7.55 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Ashiana Housing's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 59.53 crore in Q2 FY25 as against Rs 351.02 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises' net profit up 2.29% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Brigade Enterprises' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,138.13 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 19.16 per cent from Rs 1,407.92 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Arkade Developers' net profit dips 9.38% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Arkade Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 203.33 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 3.66 per cent from Rs 211.06 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: China announces tax policies to boost property market: state media
news.para: China announced new tax policies on Wednesday to bolster its struggling property market.  The measures include enhancing deed tax incentives for homebuyers and reducing the minimum prepayment rate of land value-added tax for real estate companies. These actions aim to stimulate housing demand and ease financial pressures within the sector.

news.title: NBCC signs MoU with Income Tax Department for Rs 263 crore project in Kanpur
news.para: The estimated value to the project is Rs 263 crore. It is set to be completed within 30 months from the start date.

news.title: US: Supreme Court declines to hear clash over New York rent stabilization laws
news.para: The justices turned away appeals by property owners of lower court rulings that found the city's price and eviction controls do not violate what is known as the "takings clause" of the U.S. Constitution's Fifth Amendment, which bars the government from taking property without compensating owners.

news.title: EOW books Mid City Heights's director in Rs 55 crore redevelopment fraud in Mumbai
news.para: According to the officials, Amarjit Shukla and his company Mid City Heights had been chosen to redevelop a building at Yari Road in Versova in the western suburbs and they had promised homes to the residents within a stipulated time

news.title: Balaramapuram landowners await compensation for road widening  project
news.para: Despite assurances, around 80 landowners are yet to receive compensation from the district administration's revenue department, leading to frustration and plans for protests if delays persist.

news.title: Haryana government preparing blueprint to provide 100 sq yard plots to two lakh beneficiaries
news.para: Under the initiative, eligible applicants without land will receive plots measuring 100 square yards each in the villages. Under the Mukhyamantri Gramin Awas Yojna, 5,00,000 individuals have applied for plots in the state.

news.title: NBCC India's net profit grows 52.78% in Q2 FY25
news.para: NBCC (India)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,525.95 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 18.35 per cent from Rs 2,134.36 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
